## Summary

The authentication features were already fully implemented in the codebase. I added **token rotation improvements**:

### New Session Management (`internal/handlers/session.go`)
- `GET /api/auth/sessions` - List all active sessions
- `POST /api/auth/sessions/revoke?id=<session_id>` - Revoke a specific session
- `POST /api/auth/sessions/revoke-all` - Revoke all sessions (logout everywhere)
- `POST /api/auth/sessions/rotate` - Manually rotate tokens
- `GET /api/auth/sessions/count` - Get active session count

### Token Rotation Improvements (`internal/handlers/auth.go`)
- Refresh tokens are now **revoked on use** - each refresh generates new tokens and invalidates the old refresh token
- This prevents token replay attacks

### Existing Auth Features (Already Implemented)
- OAuth (Google, GitHub) - `oauth.go`
- 2FA with TOTP + recovery codes - `twofactor.go`
- Password reset flow - `password.go`
- Email verification - `password.go`
- JWT + refresh tokens - `auth.go`
- Rate limiting middleware - `middleware/ratelimit.go`
- Security headers - `middleware/security.go`

### Tests & Linting
- Build: ✅
- Linting: ✅
- Tests: ✅
