Completed the maintenance and new feature:

**MAINTENANCE:**
1. Fixed `auth_test.go` - Added proper error handling for `json.Marshal` calls
2. Ran `golangci-lint` - All checks pass
3. Ran all tests - All pass

**NEW FEATURE - User Status Endpoint:**
- Added `UserStatusModel` to `models.go` with status types: `online`, `away`, `dnd`, `invisible`, `offline`
- Added support for custom status text (max 150 chars) and emoji
- Added status expiration for temporary statuses (e.g., "away for 30 minutes")
- Created `status.go` handler with endpoints:
  - `GET /api/status` - Get current user's status
  - `POST /api/status/update` - Update status (status, text, emoji, expiresIn)
  - `GET /api/status/user?user_id=X` - Get another user's status
- Created comprehensive tests in `status_test.go` (9 test cases)
- Registered routes in `main.go`

Changes pushed to:
- Server: `https://github.com/enclavr/server/commit/f9c7d63`
- Root: `https://github.com/enclavr/enclavr/commit/f78340e`
